4... Be7
{ Black is looking to play ...Bg5! on the next turn and get rid of the bishop! This is exactly why we started with @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/3P4/8/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKBNR b KQkq d3 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1...c5  and not  1...Nf6  − the goal was to keep that knight in its original position in order to keep the  maneuver ...Bf8-e7-g5 available! Now, White can either just keep developing, or try to prevent our plan. }
5. Nf3
{ By developing the knight here, White is taking the g5-square under control, making it impossible for us to trade off the bishops as we wanted to. }
