5... Bg5 6. f4 { Possible but not great. } 6... exf4 7. gxf4 Bh4+ 8. Kd2
{ White's king is reasonably safe since the center is pretty closed, but why would you want to start such an adventure? White could try to trap the bishop with Nf3, so it's important we realize that making a move like ...Nf6 too soon can cut it off.  Or maybe we will go ...Nf6 regardless, but we need to have a pretty specific plan after that! }
8... Nh6
{ I like the idea of making this move since Black is immediately preparing ...f7-f5! }
9. Nc3 O-O 10. Nf3 Bg4
{ With ...f7-f5 coming next, the position is about to open up, and the king on d2 clearly won't be happy! }
