9... Bg4 { Black follows the aforementioned plan. } 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Bxf3
{ Here two continuations are good. } 11... Nbd7
{ This is also a good move. I just prefer reserving that square for the other knight. }
12. a4
{ White grabs space on the queenside in advance, looking to discourage ...b7-b5. }
12... a6 13. Qc2 c4
{ With ...Rc8 and ...Nc5 coming next, Black seems very comfortable. We will try to jump into d3 or b3 with the knight, and then go ...Nf6-d7-c5/e5, activating the other knight as well as the bishop on g7 as in 0-1 Inarkiev-Dubov, Satka 2018. }
