{ Usually, this check is rather annoying. Typically, it's important for Black to be able to go ...Bg4, trade off the knight, and then the bishops with ...Bg5. Hence, having to play ...Nbd7 or ...Bd7, which prevents the setup with ...Bg4, is rather awkward. However, this time Black is not looking to play ...Bg4, but instead use a different plan, so the check is not a problem. }
4... Nd7 5. a4
